cs.CR, cs.SE, cs.LG, cs.PL, cs.CY 

This paper deals with the problem of authorship attribution of small, incomplete source code fragments, which has implications for privacy in collaborative environments such as GitHub. The paper proposes a technique for attribution and demonstrates its effectiveness through experiments. The paper is likely to be classified under cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) due to its focus on privacy, cs.SE (Software Engineering) due to its focus on version control systems and collaborative environments, cs.LG (Machine Learning) due to its use of ensembling and averaging techniques, cs.PL (Programming Languages) due to its focus on source code fragments, and cs.CY (Computers and Society) due to its implications for privacy and security in collaborative environments.
